## üß± SOLID PRINCIPLES (Frontend Adapted)

### S ‚Äî Single Responsibility
- Components and hooks must have only one reason to change.
- Extract subcomponents or custom hooks when complexity grows.

### O ‚Äî Open/Closed
- Components should be extendable via props and composition.
- Avoid modifying internal logic repeatedly.

### L ‚Äî Liskov Substitution
- Maintain consistent prop contracts across interchangeable components.
- Avoid breaking component compatibility.

### I ‚Äî Interface Segregation
- Keep prop interfaces small and specific.
- Do not force components to accept props they don't need.

### D ‚Äî Dependency Inversion
- Business logic should live in hooks or utilities.
- Components should depend on abstractions, not concrete implementations.
